# UI & Styling Guidelines

## Component Library

- Use **shadcn/ui** components (Button, Dialog, Input, etc.) before custom ones
- All shadcn/ui primitives are in `/components/ui/`
- Build custom components in `/components/shared/` for reusability

## Styling

- Use **TailwindCSS** for all styling; prefer utility classes
- Use `cn()` helper (clsx + tailwind-merge) for conditional classes
- Implement responsive design (mobile-first approach)
- Use **cva** (class-variance-authority) for reusable component variants

## Responsive Design

```tsx
// Mobile-first approach
<div className="flex flex-col md:flex-row lg:gap-4">
  <div className="w-full md:w-1/2">Content</div>
</div>
```

## Component Variants with CVA

```tsx
import { cva, type VariantProps } from "class-variance-authority";

const buttonVariants = cva(
  "rounded font-medium transition",
  {
    variants: {
      variant: {
        default: "bg-primary text-primary-foreground hover:bg-primary/90",
        outline: "border border-input hover:bg-accent",
      },
      size: {
        default: "h-10 px-4 py-2",
        sm: "h-9 px-3",
        lg: "h-11 px-8",
      },
    },
    defaultVariants: {
      variant: "default",
      size: "default",
    },
  }
);
```

## Accessibility

- Follow accessibility best practices (keyboard navigation, ARIA attributes)
- Always connect `<Label>` with inputs via `htmlFor`
- Ensure proper focus management
- Use semantic HTML elements

## Images

- Optimize images: use Next.js `<Image>` component
- Prefer WebP format when possible
- Always specify width and height
